title: License required
context: §465-2 License required. Except as otherwise provided in this chapter, it shall be unlawful to represent one&rsquo;s self as a psychologist or engage in the practice of psychology without having first obtained a license as provided in this chapter. [L 1967, c 290, pt of §1; HRS §465-2; am L 1971, c 84, §2; am L 1985, c 115, §4]
